  "text": "The patient lies in a supine position with his head elevated to 30 . The arm is then abducted to 90 , externally rotated to 90 and forward flexed to 30 , initiating the reduction. If the shoulder remains unreduced, the practitioner applies longitudinal traction. If this is unsuccessful the practitioner can place his hand in the axilla of the patient and apply pressure to the humeral head, pushing it in superolateral direction. [CITATION_1] ",
